lm_trigger","context":"Use CALM to lower stress, settle the nervous system, and reinforce the recovery signal for the body."},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":4,"title":"Sleep Preparation","duration":"30 minutes","instructions":["Tonight aim to sleep before 11 PM.","Before sleeping:","Turn off screens 30 minutes before bed.","Allow your body to relax.","Maintain a consistent sleep time.","Purpose:","supports hormone recovery improves skin repair promotes deeper sleep"],"whyThisWorks":"Consistent sleep supports hormone balance, skin repair, and overnight recovery."},{"type":"close","message":"Day 6 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"Build facial muscle endurance and circulation by increasing the number of exercise sets while\nmaintaining body movement and calmness.\nRegular facial muscle training helps support:\n- stronger cheek muscles\n- improved skin firmness\n- better blood circulation to the face\n- gradual facial lifting effect\nConsistency over time allows the facial muscles to become stronger and more toned."}]'::jsonb
