LM to lower stress, settle the nervous system, and reinforce the recovery signal for the body."},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":4,"title":"Sleep Preparation","duration":"30 minutes","instructions":["Tonight aim to sleep before 11 PM.","Before sleeping:","Turn off screens 30 minutes before bed.","Allow your body to relax.","Maintain a consistent sleep time.","Purpose:","supports hormone recovery improves skin repair promotes deeper sleep"],"whyThisWorks":"Consistent sleep supports hormone balance, skin repair, and overnight recovery."},{"type":"close","message":"Day 8 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"Further improve facial muscle strength and circulation by increasing the exercise volume while\nmaintaining daily walking, calmness, and healthy sleep habits.\nGradual progression helps support:\n- stronger cheek muscles\n- improved facial firmness\n- better circulation to the skin\n- natural facial lifting over time\nConsistency is the key to building facial muscle endurance."}]'::jsonb
