s.","Slightly lift the outer corners of the eyes upward.","Hold the lifted position firmly.","Hold for 8–10 seconds, then relax."],"reps":"10 repetitions per set - 19 sets total"}]},{"type":"calm_trigger","context":"Use CALM to lower stress, settle the nervous system, and reinforce the recovery signal for the body."},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":4,"title":"Sleep Preparation","duration":"30 minutes","instructions":["Tonight aim to sleep before 11 PM.","Before sleeping:","Turn off screens 30 minutes before bed.","Allow the body to relax.","Maintain a consistent sleep schedule.","Purpose:","supports hormone recovery improves skin repair promotes deeper sleep"],"whyThisWorks":"Consistent sleep supports hormone balance, skin repair, and overnight recovery."},{"type":"close","message":"Day 21 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"Activate and strengthen the muscles around the eyes and upper cheeks while maintaining daily\nwalking, calm practice, and consistent sleep habits.\nThese muscles support the upper face and help maintain facial balance. Strengthening them helps\nsupport:\n- improved upper cheek firmness\n- stronger eye area muscles\n- better circulation in the upper face\n- improved facial tone\nConsistent facial training helps the face gradually appear more refreshed and energized."}]'::jsonb
