ownward with your fingers.","Try to lift your eyebrows upward while slightly opening the eyes wider.","Hold for 8–10 seconds, then relax."],"reps":"10 repetitions per set - 36 sets total"}]},{"type":"calm_trigger","context":"Use CALM to lower stress, settle the nervous system, and reinforce the recovery signal for the body."},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":4,"title":"Sleep Preparation","duration":"30 minutes","instructions":["Tonight aim to sleep before 11 PM.","Before sleeping:","Turn off screens 30 minutes before bed.","Allow your body to relax.","Maintain a consistent sleep time.","Purpose:","supports hormone recovery improves skin repair promotes deeper sleep"],"whyThisWorks":"Consistent sleep supports hormone balance, skin repair, and overnight recovery."},{"type":"close","message":"Day 38 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"Activate and strengthen the eye and forehead muscles together while maintaining daily walking,\ncalm practice, and consistent sleep habits.\nThese muscles help support the upper facial structure. Strengthening them helps support:\n- improved upper facial tone\n- stronger eye support muscles\n- better circulation in the upper face\n- improved facial muscle coordination\nConsistent facial activation helps the face gradually appear more refreshed and balanced."}]'::jsonb
