rd.","Hold the position firmly.","Keep the cheek muscles engaged.","Hold for 8–10 seconds, then relax.","Alternate sides for each repetition."],"reps":"10 repetitions per set - 37 sets total"}]},{"type":"calm_trigger","context":"Use CALM to lower stress, settle the nervous system, and reinforce the recovery signal for the body."},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":4,"title":"Sleep Preparation","duration":"30 minutes","instructions":["Tonight aim to sleep before 11 PM.","Before sleeping:","Turn off screens 30 minutes before bed.","Allow your body to relax.","Maintain a consistent sleep schedule.","Purpose:","supports hormone recovery improves skin repair promotes deeper sleep"],"whyThisWorks":"Consistent sleep supports hormone balance, skin repair, and overnight recovery."},{"type":"close","message":"Day 39 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"Activate and strengthen the mouth and cheek coordination muscles while maintaining daily walking,\ncalm practice, and consistent sleep habits.\nThe muscles around the mouth connect closely with the cheeks and mid-face. Strengthening them\nhelps support:\n- improved cheek support\n- stronger smile muscles\n- better circulation in the mid-face\n- improved facial muscle coordination\nConsistent facial activation helps the face gradually appear more toned and balanced."}]'::jsonb
)
