ing.","Feel the stretch in the neck and jawline area.","Hold for 8–10 seconds, then relax."],"reps":"10 repetitions per set - 38 sets total"}]},{"type":"calm_trigger","context":"Use CALM to lower stress, settle the nervous system, and reinforce the recovery signal for the body."},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":4,"title":"Sleep Preparation","duration":"30 minutes","instructions":["Tonight aim to sleep before 11 PM.","Before sleeping:","Turn off screens 30 minutes before bed.","Allow your body to relax.","Maintain a consistent sleep time.","Purpose:","supports hormone recovery improves skin repair promotes deeper sleep"],"whyThisWorks":"Consistent sleep supports hormone balance, skin repair, and overnight recovery."},{"type":"close","message":"Day 40 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"Activate and strengthen the neck and jawline muscles while maintaining daily walking, calm\npractice, and consistent sleep habits.\nThe neck and jawline muscles support the structure of the lower face. Strengthening them helps\nsupport:\n- improved jawline firmness\n- stronger neck muscles\n- better circulation in the lower face\n- improved facial posture\nConsistent facial and neck activation helps the face gradually appear more lifted and structured."}]'::jsonb
