uth gently.","Slide your lower jaw slowly to the right side.","Hold the position firmly.","Hold for 8–10 seconds, then relax.","Alternate sides with each repetition."],"reps":"10 repetitions per set - 83 sets total"}]},{"type":"calm_trigger","context":"Use CALM to lower stress, settle the nervous system, and reinforce the recovery signal for the body."},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":4,"title":"Sleep Preparation","duration":"30 minutes","instructions":["Tonight aim to sleep before 11 PM.","Before sleeping:","Turn off screens 30 minutes before bed.","Allow your body to relax.","Maintain a consistent sleep time.","Purpose:","supports hormone recovery improves skin repair promotes deeper sleep"],"whyThisWorks":"Consistent sleep supports hormone balance, skin repair, and overnight recovery."},{"type":"close","message":"Day 84 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"Activate and strengthen the jawline and lower face muscles while maintaining daily walking, calm\npractice, and consistent sleep habits.\nThe jawline muscles support the structure of the lower face and help maintain facial balance.\nStrengthening them helps support:\n- improved jawline firmness\n- stronger lower facial muscles\n- better circulation in the lower face\n- improved facial muscle stability\nConsistent facial activation helps the face gradually appear more defined and structured."}]'::jsonb
