n muscles gently.","Hold the position for 8–10 seconds, then relax."],"reps":"10 repetitions per set - 84 sets total"}]},{"type":"calm_trigger","context":"Use CALM to lower stress, settle the nervous system, and reinforce the recovery signal for the body."},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":4,"title":"Sleep Preparation","duration":"30 minutes","instructions":["Tonight aim to sleep before 11 PM.","Before sleeping:","Turn off screens 30 minutes before bed.","Allow your body to relax.","Maintain a consistent sleep schedule.","Purpose:","supports hormone recovery improves skin repair promotes deeper sleep"],"whyThisWorks":"Consistent sleep supports hormone balance, skin repair, and overnight recovery."},{"type":"close","message":"Day 85 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"Activate and strengthen the neck and chin muscles while maintaining daily walking, calm practice,\nand consistent sleep habits.\nThe neck and chin muscles help support the lower face and improve facial posture. Strengthening\nthem helps support:\n- improved chin firmness\n- stronger neck muscles\n- better circulation in the lower face\n- improved jawline definition\nConsistent facial activation helps the face gradually appear more lifted and structured."}]'::jsonb
)
